
# MrBase64

![MrBase64 mascot](Assets.xcassets/MascotCharacter.imageset/mascot-character.png)

MrBase64 is a compact macOS utility (SwiftUI) that converts images into Base64 and provides two convenient output formats: raw Base64 or a Markdown reference-style data-URL. It's designed to be lightweight and focused — drop an image, choose a format, and copy the result.

## Project summary

- Encode image files to Base64 for embedding or processing ✅
- Toggle between **Base64** or **Markdown** (reference-style) output ✅
- Markdown references are generated from the filename (without extension) plus a `yyMMdd-HHmmss` timestamp for uniqueness ✅
- Output preference is persisted using `@AppStorage` between launches ✅
- When no image is loaded a friendly mascot (Mr. Base64) is shown in the UI ✅
- The main window is fixed-size (non-resizable) and the app quits when the main window is closed ✅

## Quick start

1. Build and run from Xcode or use the command line:

```bash
xcodebuild -scheme MrBase64 -configuration Debug build
open "$(xcodebuild -scheme MrBase64 -configuration Debug -showBuildSettings | awk -F= '/BUILT_PRODUCTS_DIR/{print $2}' | tr -d ' ')/MrBase64.app"
```

2. Drop an image onto the app window (or use File → Open).
3. Choose **Base64** or **Markdown** from the format control.
4. Click **Copy** to copy the selected output to the clipboard.

> Example Markdown output (reference-style):
>
> ```markdown
> ![photo.jpg][photo-251221-103015]
>
> [photo-251221-103015]: data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD...
> ```

## Linting & formatting

The project includes a basic lint and format configuration and a GitHub Actions job that enforces them on push/PR to `main`:

- `.swiftlint.yml` — SwiftLint configuration
- `.swiftformat` — SwiftFormat configuration
- `.github/workflows/lint.yml` — CI job that runs `swiftlint lint --strict` and `swiftformat --lint .`

Locally, install SwiftLint and SwiftFormat (Homebrew) and run:

```bash
brew install swiftlint swiftformat
swiftlint lint --strict
swiftformat --lint .
```

You can optionally run `swiftformat .` to automatically reformat the code.

---

## Notes on UI

- The main window is intentionally fixed-size (non-resizable) to keep the UI compact.
- When the window is closed the app will quit automatically.
- The mascot image is embedded in the asset catalog (`Assets.xcassets/MascotCharacter.imageset/mascot-character.png`) and is displayed when no image is loaded.

---

## Supported image formats

PNG, JPEG, HEIC, HEIF, AVIF, WebP, TIFF, GIF and other `public.image` types supported via `UniformTypeIdentifiers`.

## Files of interest

- `MrBase64App.swift` — app lifecycle, window behavior (non-resizable), and file-open integration

- `Info.plist` — app metadata and document types (`CFBundleTypeRole: Viewer`)

- `Assets.xcassets/MascotCharacter.imageset/` — mascot image asset (add @2x for Retina if desired)

- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — build & test CI
- `.github/workflows/lint.yml` — lint/format CI
- `Tests/UnitTests/Base64EncoderTests.swift` — unit tests for encoding/mime detection
